PROJECT 2: TIC-TAC-TOE AI
Title
Tic-Tac-Toe Game with Computer Opponent Using C

Objective
To develop a Tic-Tac-Toe game where a human player competes against a computer opponent.

Description
Tic-Tac-Toe is a popular two-player game played on a 3×3 grid. In this project, the user plays against the computer. The program checks for winning conditions and declares the winner.

Algorithm
Initialize the game board.
Display the board.
Accept player's move.
Update the board.
Check if the player wins.
Computer selects an available position.
Check if computer wins.
Repeat until the game ends.

  Source Code
#include <stdio.h>

char board[3][3] = {
    {'1','2','3'},
    {'4','5','6'},
    {'7','8','9'}
};

void displayBoard()
{
    printf("\n");
    for(int i=0;i<3;i++)
    {
        printf(" %c | %c | %c ",board[i][0],board[i][1],board[i][2]);

        if(i<2)
            printf("\n---|---|---\n");
    }
    printf("\n");
}

int checkWin()
{
    for(int i=0;i<3;i++)
    {
        if(board[i][0]==board[i][1] &&
           board[i][1]==board[i][2])
            return 1;

        if(board[0][i]==board[1][i] &&
           board[1][i]==board[2][i])
            return 1;
    }

    if(board[0][0]==board[1][1] &&
       board[1][1]==board[2][2])
        return 1;

    if(board[0][2]==board[1][1] &&
       board[1][1]==board[2][0])
        return 1;

    return 0;
}

void placeMark(int pos,char mark)
{
    int row=(pos-1)/3;
    int col=(pos-1)%3;
    board[row][col]=mark;
}

int main()
{
    int pos;

    while(1)
    {
        displayBoard();

        printf("Enter position for X: ");
        scanf("%d",&pos);

        placeMark(pos,'X');

        if(checkWin())
        {
            displayBoard();
            printf("Player Wins!\n");
            break;
        }

        for(int i=0;i<3;i++)
        {
            for(int j=0;j<3;j++)
            {
                if(board[i][j]!='X' &&
                   board[i][j]!='O')
                {
                    board[i][j]='O';
                    goto endloop;
                }
            }
        }

        endloop:

        if(checkWin())
        {
            displayBoard();
            printf("Computer Wins!\n");
            break;
        }
    }

    return 0;
}
